text:
1833 West Farms Road, adjoining the S.W. corner of East 176th Street, showing the West Farms Mission House. The house was demolished and on its site now (1937) stands a 3-story brick garage. The mission occupied the site of the southern half of the garage building.

1915.
title: Bronx: West Farms Road.

text:
1833 West Farms Road, adjoining the S.W. corner of East 176th Street. The frame house has been demolished and on its site now (1937) stands a 3-story brick garage building. The exact site of the house is in the northern half of the garage.

May 31, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Bronx: West Farms Road - No. 1853.
